 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# How to compute and plot the volume of the brain substructures?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "\n",
    "import polpo.preprocessing.pd as ppd\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing import IndexMap, NestingSwapper\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.dict import DictMap, DictMerger\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.load.pregnancy import (\n",
    "    FIRST_STRUCTS,\n",
    "    DenseMaternalCsvDataLoader,\n",
    "    DenseMaternalMeshLoader,\n",
    ")\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.mesh.io import PvReader"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Loading meshes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "subject_id = \"01\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# side, struct, time\n",
    "meshes = {True: {}, False: {}}  # bool represents side\n",
    "for left in meshes.keys():\n",
    "    for struct in FIRST_STRUCTS:\n",
    "        file_finder = DenseMaternalMeshLoader(\n",
    "            subject_id=subject_id,\n",
    "            as_dict=True,\n",
    "            left=left,\n",
    "            struct=struct,\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "        pipe = file_finder + DictMap(PvReader())\n",
    "\n",
    "        meshes[left][struct] = pipe()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Loading tabular data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pilot = subject_id == \"01\"\n",
    "\n",
    "pipe = DenseMaternalCsvDataLoader(pilot=pilot, subject_id=subject_id)\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pipe()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here, we filter the tabular data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "session_selector = ppd.DfIsInFilter(\"stage\", [\"post\"], negation=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "predictor_selector = (\n",
    "    session_selector + ppd.ColumnsSelector(\"gestWeek\") + ppd.SeriesToDict()\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_dict = predictor_selector(df)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Plot results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 4500x1800 with 21 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "_, axes = plt.subplots(\n",
    "    nrows=2 + 1,\n",
    "    ncols=len(FIRST_STRUCTS),\n",
    "    sharex=False,\n",
    "    sharey=False,\n",
    "    squeeze=True,\n",
    "    figsize=(30, 12),\n",
    "    dpi=150,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "dataset_pipe = (\n",
    "    DictMerger() + NestingSwapper() + IndexMap(lambda x: np.array(x), index=0)\n",
    ")\n",
    "model = LinearRegression(fit_intercept=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "for left, meshes_structs in meshes.items():\n",
    "    side_name = \"L\" if left else \"R\"\n",
    "    for pos, (struct, meshes_struct) in enumerate(meshes_structs.items()):\n",
    "        ax = axes[int(left)][pos]\n",
    "\n",
    "        x, meshes_ = dataset_pipe((x_dict, meshes_struct))\n",
    "\n",
    "        volumes = [mesh.volume for mesh in meshes_]\n",
    "\n",
    "        model.fit(x[:, None], volumes)\n",
    "\n",
    "        x_pred = np.linspace(min(x), max(x))\n",
    "\n",
    "        ax.scatter(x, volumes)\n",
    "        ax.plot(x_pred, model.predict(x_pred[:, None]))\n",
    "\n",
    "        if pos == 0:\n",
    "            ax.set_ylabel(\"Volume\")\n",
    "\n",
    "        ax.set_title(f\"{subject_id}, {struct}, {side_name}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# L + R\n",
    "for pos, struct in enumerate(FIRST_STRUCTS):\n",
    "    ax = axes[2][pos]\n",
    "\n",
    "    x, meshes_left, meshes_right = dataset_pipe(\n",
    "        (x_dict, meshes[True][struct], meshes[False][struct])\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    volumes = [\n",
    "        left_mesh.volume + right_mesh.volume\n",
    "        for left_mesh, right_mesh in zip(meshes_left, meshes_right)\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\n",
    "    model.fit(x[:, None], volumes)\n",
    "\n",
    "    x_pred = np.linspace(min(x), max(x))\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.scatter(x, volumes, color=\"orange\")\n",
    "    ax.plot(x_pred, model.predict(x_pred[:, None]), color=\"orange\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    if pos == 0:\n",
    "        ax.set_ylabel(\"Volume\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel(\"Gestational week\")\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f\"{subject_id}, {struct}, R+L\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
